    "# Importation de modules n√©cessaires\n",

    "\n",
    "#¬†Vecteur des abscisses : un point tous les 0,1 s entre 0 et 10 s\n",
    "t = np.arange(0, 10, 0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fr√©quence de la sinuso√Øde\n",
    "f = 0.3\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sinuso√Øde : c'est tout simple, il suffit d'√©crire l'expression math√©matique üòé\n",
    "w = np.sin(2*math.pi*f*t)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Affichage du signal\n",
    "plt.plot(t,w)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Des l√©gendes, c'est toujours bien !\n",

    "plt.ylabel(\"w(t)\")\n",

    "    y(t) = A e^{-at} \\sin(2 \\pi f t)\n",

    "\n",
    "  Utilisez `numpy.multiply` pour effectuer la multiplication des deux signaux (l'exponentielle et le sinus).\n",
    "  √âtudiez l'influence des param√®tres sur la forme du signal."

   "source": [
    "t = np.arange(0, 10, 0.01)\n",
    "params = [[2, .5, 2], [2, 2, 2], [2, .5, 1]]\n",
    "for p in params:\n",
    "    A, a, f = p\n",
    "    y1 = np.exp(-a*t)\n",
    "    y2 = np.sin(2*math.pi*f*t)\n",
    "    y = A * np.multiply(y1, y2)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.plot(t,y)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"y(t)\")\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"A = {A}, a = {a}, f = {f}\")\n",
    "    plt.show()"
